      <p>A low credit score can feel like a wall between you and the financial help you need. But having bad credit - generally defined as a FICO score below 580 - doesn't mean you're locked out of the lending market entirely. A growing number of lenders specialize in working with borrowers who have imperfect credit histories, and some offer surprisingly competitive terms. The key is knowing where to look and what to watch out for.</p>
 
