      <p>A bad credit score doesn't have to be permanent, and the right credit card can actually be one of the most effective tools for rebuilding it. By opening a card designed for bad or limited credit, using it responsibly, and paying on time every month, you can build a positive payment history that steadily improves your score - often enough to qualify for mainstream products within 12–24 months. The key is choosing the right product and using it correctly.</p>
 
